WEBVTT

00:25.484 --> 00:27.193
Where should we go?

00:27.194 --> 00:30.113
Couldn't hear you.
What did you say?

00:30.114 --> 00:31.906
Well, where should we go?

00:31.907 --> 00:38.329
Hawaii is the obvious choice.

00:38.330 --> 00:40.749
Just think about it. Stop that.

00:40.750 --> 00:43.918
Will you stop and listen to me, please?

00:43.919 --> 00:46.671
There's a reason that people
convalesce at the beach.

00:46.672 --> 00:49.048
You'll complain about
sand getting everywhere.

00:49.049 --> 00:50.258
I'll be happy.

00:50.259 --> 00:53.053
Mmm.
Well, that's what's most important.

00:59.185 --> 01:00.936
Hurry the hell up, grandpa!

01:01.520 --> 01:05.482
The Rockies are cozy.
The cold isn't bitter there. It's warm.

01:05.483 --> 01:07.776
Cold is just cold, Joan.

01:07.777 --> 01:09.904
It's the kind of place
you could spend forever.

01:10.571 --> 01:13.198
It's 84 degrees in Naples today.

01:13.199 --> 01:14.325
Italy?

01:15.117 --> 01:18.036
- Florida.
- We're not Florida people, Larry.

01:18.037 --> 01:20.330
Oh, God. Joan, that sounds so snobby.

01:20.331 --> 01:22.499
We're not Florida people.

01:22.500 --> 01:25.084
You know,
you sound like Karen.

01:25.085 --> 01:27.962
Karen is my friend, and she is not well.

01:27.963 --> 01:31.884
Well, we don't have to make people
into saints ju-just because they're dying.

01:32.760 --> 01:34.011
Jesus, Larry.

01:34.720 --> 01:37.305
Look, it's got mountains and ice and snow.

01:37.306 --> 01:40.809
So many things for you to complain about.
You will love it.

01:40.810 --> 01:44.395
I don't love to complain.
That's not something people love.

01:44.396 --> 01:46.898
I don't want to fight. It's a big day.

01:46.899 --> 01:49.985
You know, people die at these things?
I saw it on the Internet.

01:50.778 --> 01:52.737
It's a gender reveal party.

01:52.738 --> 01:55.323
I mean, I get eliminating the surprise…

01:55.324 --> 01:58.409
- Can we just let them make a fuss?
- …but it's not party-worthy.

01:58.410 --> 02:02.622
You know, one of the great joys of my life
has been allowing for surprises.

02:02.623 --> 02:05.542
- Do you… Do you remember…
- Everything has to be a party nowadays.

02:05.543 --> 02:08.044
…when you were convinced
that Zach would be a girl?

02:08.045 --> 02:10.421
- Everything has to be an event.
- You just don't like parties.

02:10.422 --> 02:12.215
No. No, you just hate having fun.

02:12.216 --> 02:15.718
- Kids have preschool graduations now.
- You're only happy when you're miserable.

02:15.719 --> 02:17.720
You're five. You don't know anything.

02:17.721 --> 02:21.432
- Look, I… Can we just enjoy it? Okay?
- But, you know, you have the big party.

02:21.433 --> 02:23.643
- Big party.
- Larry!

02:23.644 --> 02:25.479
Can we just enjoy it, okay?

02:26.146 --> 02:28.147
Asshole!

02:28.148 --> 02:31.235
I'm enjoying it. I'm enjoying it.
I'm enjoying it.

02:31.986 --> 02:35.030
Joan.

02:36.240 --> 02:38.284
- We have to tell them.
- I know.

02:38.868 --> 02:40.160
Just give me today.

02:52.715 --> 02:54.340
Sam, can you grab the balloons?

02:54.341 --> 02:55.800
Yeah, I heard you.
I'm getting the balloons.

02:55.801 --> 02:57.552
- We're back.
- Hey, Larry. How's it going?

02:57.553 --> 03:00.889
- Hi. You look lovely.
- We're back. Ah, the traffic, unbel…

03:00.890 --> 03:03.057
- Oh, hi. How are you, sweetheart?
- Oh. Thank you, Mom.

03:03.058 --> 03:04.642
- Hey. Hey.
- Grandma! Grandma!

03:04.643 --> 03:07.270
Good to see you, my dears.

03:07.271 --> 03:08.980
Let's go for some cake?

03:08.981 --> 03:12.233
- Sam, the balloons.
- I have the balloons in my hand!

03:14.361 --> 03:15.987
Thanks
for agreeing to host, Pop-pop.

03:15.988 --> 03:17.947
- This is gonna be a boy.
- How do you know that?

03:17.948 --> 03:21.659
Because it's so low. A boy.

03:21.660 --> 03:24.245
So, coming up on 65 years
of marriage. Any tips?

03:24.246 --> 03:26.581
You burst one of those balloons
and you'll never find out!

03:27.833 --> 03:29.792
Oh! Uh, Nana,

03:29.793 --> 03:32.420
we found a bunch of your old pictures
in the basement.

03:32.421 --> 03:33.589
Thanks, sweetie.

03:34.256 --> 03:35.340
Who is that?

03:35.341 --> 03:36.799
Pop-pop was in the army?

03:36.800 --> 03:40.887
No, sweetie. That was Nana's
stupidly attractive first husband.

03:40.888 --> 03:43.097
Jesus Christ, he's a dapper man.

03:43.098 --> 03:44.682
Why would you leave him for Pop-pop?

03:44.683 --> 03:46.434
No, sweetie.

03:46.435 --> 03:49.605
Luke was a soldier
and, um, he died at war.

03:50.189 --> 03:52.566
Lar, you got really lucky,
my friend.

03:53.192 --> 03:55.902
I bet he would have been a good dad.

03:55.903 --> 03:58.529
That's not how biology works.

03:58.530 --> 04:00.990
Lar?

04:00.991 --> 04:02.742
Hey, he's being funny.

04:02.743 --> 04:03.826
Shut up, Zach.

04:03.827 --> 04:05.328
- Larry, are you okay?
- Dad?

04:05.329 --> 04:07.205
- Dad?
- Larry! Larry!

04:08.582 --> 04:09.583
Larry!

04:30.479 --> 04:32.106
Guess you weren't expecting it?

04:32.940 --> 04:35.608
What the hell is going on? Where's Joan?

04:35.609 --> 04:38.403
Ladies and gentlemen,
we have now reached the junction.

04:38.404 --> 04:40.238
Please alight the train

04:40.239 --> 04:42.074
where your eternity lies ahead.

04:42.992 --> 04:44.742
I don't remember buying a train ticket.

04:46.787 --> 04:49.289
Well, I guess
the surgery didn't go so well.

05:13.897 --> 05:18.318
Mind your step.
Disorientation is normal.

05:22.364 --> 05:26.784
The newly dead from North America,
arriving in Junction 301.

05:26.785 --> 05:28.327
What is going on?

05:28.328 --> 05:32.290
Hey. All the fun of the Middle Ages
with none of the leprosy. Come on.

05:32.291 --> 05:34.834
Hey, you want to party?
Party all night, party for all time.

05:34.835 --> 05:36.711
Hey, pally. Good to see you.
You must be new.

05:36.712 --> 05:37.962
- Where am I?
- Jessica?

05:37.963 --> 05:39.589
He hasn't made contact yet.

05:39.590 --> 05:40.673
Jessica?

05:40.674 --> 05:42.884
- W-What is this?
- Your AC will be with you shortly.

05:42.885 --> 05:44.927
- Welcome, Sandro. Follow me.
- Hi. Can you help me? I--

05:44.928 --> 05:46.554
Your AC will be with you shortly.

05:46.555 --> 05:49.015
- Are you an AC?
- Yes, but I'm not your AC.

05:49.016 --> 05:50.600
- Come.
- Jessica?

06:00.736 --> 06:04.782
Final call for
the Dingle World, 174.

06:09.661 --> 06:11.287
Hi. Do you work here?

06:11.288 --> 06:13.998
No, honey. I'm here for my health.

06:13.999 --> 06:16.085
Listen.
I think I've been abducted.

06:16.668 --> 06:18.461
You haven't been abducted.

06:18.462 --> 06:21.589
Well, where's my family?
Where's Joan? Where am I?

06:21.590 --> 06:24.342
You're in the junction. Your AC will be--

06:24.343 --> 06:25.886
Be with me shortly. Yeah.

06:34.019 --> 06:37.356
Next arrival in 15 minutes.

06:44.655 --> 06:49.618
Final train from Junction 301,
departing in five minutes.

06:50.327 --> 06:52.954
Oh, Jill. This is all noise.

06:52.955 --> 06:54.038
I know you, Jill.

06:54.039 --> 06:56.249
You just want a box of Chardonnay
and a pool.

06:56.250 --> 06:57.959
I do like Chardonnay.

06:57.960 --> 07:00.086
Well, then I have the eternity for you.

07:00.087 --> 07:01.130
Okay.

07:02.923 --> 07:04.174
Yeah. Okay.

07:05.134 --> 07:06.135
Straight ahead.

07:08.554 --> 07:09.679
Oh. Sorry.

07:12.975 --> 07:14.143
You little bitch.

07:16.395 --> 07:18.729
Uh… Larry Cutler?

07:18.730 --> 07:20.898
Is there a Larry Cutler here?

07:20.899 --> 07:22.316
- That's me.
- Larry?

07:22.317 --> 07:24.735
- That's me.
- Oh! Hey, man. I'm so sorry.

07:24.736 --> 07:26.571
They had me at a whole 'nother gate.

07:26.572 --> 07:27.655
Who are you?

07:27.656 --> 07:29.198
I'm Anna. I'm your AC.

07:29.199 --> 07:31.910
- What does that stand for?
- Your afterlife coordinator.

07:32.786 --> 07:33.870
That's not a job.

07:33.871 --> 07:35.329
You've passed away, Larry.

07:35.330 --> 07:36.581
No.

07:36.582 --> 07:37.582
You're dead.

07:37.583 --> 07:40.252
No. I'm not. I-I hit my head. And…

07:41.587 --> 07:42.670
It's a girl.

07:42.671 --> 07:43.922
Walk with me.

07:45.549 --> 07:48.634
Oh. All right, listen.
So I was sitting with my family,

07:48.635 --> 07:50.136
- and then I, uh--
- Died.

07:50.137 --> 07:52.139
No, and I… Whatever you're trying to pro…

07:53.432 --> 07:54.807
It's not sore. Weird.

07:54.808 --> 07:55.851
Look, Larry.

07:58.312 --> 07:59.396
How is this happening?

08:00.022 --> 08:03.274
When you get here,
your form reverts to its happiest self.

08:03.275 --> 08:04.483
It could be any age.

08:04.484 --> 08:06.319
That's why there are lots
of 10-year-old boys,

08:06.320 --> 08:07.820
but not a lot of teenagers though.

08:07.821 --> 08:10.781
Ah, shit. Joan. Joan, my wife.
I need… I need to go back.

08:10.782 --> 08:13.367
Oh, Larry. Look on the bright side.
At least your penis works again.

08:13.368 --> 08:14.745
- Hey, Anna.
- My…

08:15.329 --> 08:16.996
My penis always worked.

08:16.997 --> 08:19.333
There's no need to feel shame here.
We've seen it all.

08:20.167 --> 08:21.626
Uh. Yeah. Well, if I was dead,

08:21.627 --> 08:24.587
I wouldn't really care
about the functionality of my…

08:24.588 --> 08:26.130
- Penis.
- Ugh.

08:26.131 --> 08:29.300
I wouldn't be embarrassed
and annoyed with you right now,

08:29.301 --> 08:32.346
because you're not supposed
to be annoyed in heaven.

08:32.971 --> 08:35.390
Oh, they tell you such strange things
down there.

08:36.141 --> 08:38.060
Larry, what is a soul?

08:39.770 --> 08:40.771
Uh…

08:41.563 --> 08:45.942
I don't know. I suppose
it's the perfect version of yourself.

08:45.943 --> 08:47.945
No. It's just you.

08:50.364 --> 08:51.697
No, that can't be right.

08:51.698 --> 08:55.076
If you were annoyed a lot in life, Larry,
then you might be annoyed a lot in death.

08:55.077 --> 08:56.661
Were you annoyed a lot in life, Larry?

08:56.662 --> 08:58.329
Listen to me. My wife really
needs me right now.

08:58.330 --> 08:59.789
I'm sorry. It doesn't work like that.

08:59.790 --> 09:02.709
Wake up, Larry. Wake up. Wake up.
Come on, buddy. Come on.

09:03.919 --> 09:05.002
What the hell is that?

09:05.003 --> 09:07.129
If you were dreaming,
you wouldn't feel that pain.

09:07.130 --> 09:08.589
I didn't feel that.

09:08.590 --> 09:11.217
You know, usually you old fellas really
cheer up about the whole penis thing.

09:11.218 --> 09:13.678
Listen to me, I need to talk to God, okay?
That's what I want.

09:13.679 --> 09:16.305
- I want to speak with the big guy.
- Okay, so you're one of those.

09:16.306 --> 09:18.182
I don't know why you didn't say that
in the first place.

09:18.183 --> 09:19.475
We got tons of eternities.

09:19.476 --> 09:22.144
What are you, New Testament,
Old Testament? Hindu, Buddhist?

09:22.145 --> 09:24.105
- Pick your poison.
- Hold on. Is God not real?

09:24.106 --> 09:25.273
I don't know. But, listen,

09:25.274 --> 09:27.400
after a couple hundred years
in one of these eternities,

09:27.401 --> 09:28.944
you won't even know the difference.

09:29.861 --> 09:31.529
Who do you work for?

09:31.530 --> 09:32.697
I work for Frank.

09:32.698 --> 09:34.490
Okay, then, uh, who does Frank work for?

09:34.491 --> 09:37.451
Frank works for Tom.
Why-Why does it even matter? Come on.

09:37.452 --> 09:40.454
We don't have time.
I got other clients, Larry, please.

09:42.541 --> 09:43.542
Okay. Well,

09:44.459 --> 09:48.421
I'm sorry for assuming that paradise
would look a little less like life.

09:48.422 --> 09:49.588
This isn't paradise.

09:49.589 --> 09:52.550
This is just a brief transition
between life and eternity.

09:52.551 --> 09:54.928
Oh, you've earned a life
worth an eternity.

09:55.470 --> 09:57.847
- I have?
- It's just something we say.

09:57.848 --> 09:59.473
Everybody gets an eternity.

09:59.474 --> 10:00.934
The good, the bad and the ugly.

10:01.977 --> 10:04.395
So all that "live a good life" stuff's
a-a bunch of crap?

10:04.396 --> 10:05.479
Afraid so.

10:05.480 --> 10:07.732
Red door escapee.

10:07.733 --> 10:09.233
- Get away from me!
- Do not engage.

10:09.234 --> 10:11.110
- Oh, that? Don't worry about that.
- Get away!

10:11.111 --> 10:13.238
Just don't run through any red doors.

10:13.822 --> 10:15.615
I can't go back. I can't do it anymore.

10:16.491 --> 10:19.076
Come here. Come…

10:19.077 --> 10:21.121
- Get off me.
- Larry, let's go. Let's go.

10:23.332 --> 10:27.419
Final call for Alpine World, 234.

10:28.128 --> 10:30.129
So this is where I'm staying, huh?

10:30.130 --> 10:32.673
For now, until you choose
the right eternity for you.

10:32.674 --> 10:34.092
But we'll get into all that later.

10:34.718 --> 10:39.806
- I think now's a good time. I'm dead.
- Hey. There you go. Acceptance.

10:41.016 --> 10:43.100
We have some of your favorite clothes
in the closet,

10:43.101 --> 10:44.770
in case you want to check it out.

10:53.028 --> 10:54.112
Anna?

11:18.303 --> 11:21.972
Didn't 1840s Ireland have a devastating
famine caused by a potato blight

11:21.973 --> 11:24.059
and the British exporting
all their other food?

11:24.684 --> 11:27.562
Well, not here.

11:28.814 --> 11:30.940
Ever wanted to be the captain of--

11:30.941 --> 11:34.485
Do you hate clothes,
but you need them to keep warm?

11:34.486 --> 11:41.159
Well, here in Natural State 454,
it's always a balmy 72 degrees.

11:42.077 --> 11:44.413
Ooh. Looking good, Jim.

11:45.247 --> 11:46.872
He's "cardiac-ing" really hard.

11:46.873 --> 11:49.083
Suction, goddamn it.

11:50.627 --> 11:53.296
- We lost him.
- But you found me.

11:55.424 --> 11:57.675
If you suffered a violent death,

11:57.676 --> 12:00.220
please reach out
to our afterlife counselors.

12:01.138 --> 12:02.973
You know,
I did, uh, experiment in college.

12:26.329 --> 12:27.539
Hi, there.

12:28.248 --> 12:29.249
Hi.

12:30.876 --> 12:32.710
Confusing time, huh?

12:32.711 --> 12:35.297
Yes, actually.

12:38.133 --> 12:40.926
Oh. S-Sorry, I'm… I'm married.

12:42.679 --> 12:44.388
What if I, uh, told you

12:44.389 --> 12:47.183
I could secure you a spot
in the hottest eternity…

12:47.184 --> 12:50.729
Marge. You know the policy.
No selling in the bar.

12:52.981 --> 12:54.483
No selling in the bar.

13:01.072 --> 13:02.656
Something strong, please.

13:02.657 --> 13:03.867
First day?

13:05.327 --> 13:07.203
So what are you,
like an angel or something?

13:07.204 --> 13:08.205
Oh, no, no.

13:09.331 --> 13:10.415
I'm a bartender.

13:11.416 --> 13:13.418
Oh, shit. Do I have to get a job?

13:14.127 --> 13:15.587
Only if you want to stay here.

13:16.963 --> 13:19.883
So what are you thinking about,
for where you want to go from here?

13:21.760 --> 13:23.553
Oh.

13:24.387 --> 13:26.972
I don't… I don't know.

13:26.973 --> 13:29.850
Somewhere sunny with a beach, I guess.

13:29.851 --> 13:33.230
But my wife won't like that,
so I can't stay for long.

13:34.272 --> 13:36.066
Did your AC go over the rules?

13:36.650 --> 13:38.609
No, but, uh, she seemed busy.

13:38.610 --> 13:40.277
All right. Well, look, the big thing

13:40.278 --> 13:42.655
is there's no switching eternities
after you've chosen.

13:42.656 --> 13:44.824
No visiting other eternities, no nothing.

13:45.367 --> 13:47.117
Eternity is eternity.

13:47.118 --> 13:48.410
It's forever.

13:48.411 --> 13:52.248
What if I didn't go along with the rules?
What are they gonna do, kill me again?

13:52.249 --> 13:54.124
Technically they can't kill you again.

13:54.125 --> 13:55.209
But you break a rule,

13:55.210 --> 13:58.547
you overstay your welcome,
or you try switching eternities,

13:59.339 --> 14:00.799
they'll put you into the void.

14:01.383 --> 14:02.675
Is that like hell?

14:02.676 --> 14:03.843
As close as there is.

14:04.886 --> 14:07.722
It's just blackness, for eternity.

14:09.933 --> 14:10.934
Um…

14:12.811 --> 14:15.855
My wife has cancer. It's terminal.

14:17.357 --> 14:18.482
I'm sorry to hear that.

14:18.483 --> 14:22.028
Worst part about death is the guilt
you feel for the ones you left behind.

14:23.405 --> 14:26.156
I know, and I told her that I was
always gonna take care of her.

14:26.157 --> 14:29.326
And now she's sick,
and dealing with all this.

14:29.327 --> 14:31.537
Um… Could I get a mixer with that?

14:31.538 --> 14:32.998
That is absolutely disgusting.

14:36.918 --> 14:38.669
Morning, sleepyhead.

14:38.670 --> 14:40.129
Morning, sweetie.

14:44.843 --> 14:46.261
What the hell?

14:47.053 --> 14:48.637
What's going on? How did you get in here?

14:48.638 --> 14:50.682
- Larry, you don't remember?
- Remember what?

14:51.850 --> 14:53.643
No, we didn't. Did we?

14:54.227 --> 14:55.936
Nah, I'm just joking. I have a key.

14:55.937 --> 14:57.730
- Why do you have a key?
- It's not important.

14:57.731 --> 15:00.483
So, you seemed to have
a good time last night.

15:00.984 --> 15:03.652
I'm dead. You wouldn't think hangovers
would be a thing.

15:03.653 --> 15:06.031
I know, right?
It's a common misconception.

15:07.032 --> 15:09.158
I got a question.

15:09.159 --> 15:10.743
Mm-hmm. Hit me with it.

15:13.413 --> 15:17.042
So, everyone working here, they don't want
to go to their eternity. Why?

15:17.751 --> 15:20.003
Some people haven't accepted death,

15:20.670 --> 15:23.672
and some people are waiting
for their loved ones.

15:23.673 --> 15:24.757
Oh.

15:24.758 --> 15:28.887
And others haven't decided yet,
and those are the worst ones.

15:30.305 --> 15:31.639
Well, why did you stay?

15:31.640 --> 15:34.975
That is a story
for another time.

15:34.976 --> 15:36.853
- Mmm.
- So, tell me.

15:37.646 --> 15:39.481
Where you going? Did you decide?

15:42.359 --> 15:45.277
No. I… I need to see where Joan is.

15:45.278 --> 15:47.905
- Mmm.
- How can I tell how close she is?

15:47.906 --> 15:50.699
No, I'm sorry. It doesn't work like that.
I can't do that.

15:50.700 --> 15:53.827
So all that looking down from above stuff,
that's just a bunch of BS?

15:53.828 --> 15:55.537
Mmm. You're annoyed?

15:55.538 --> 15:57.164
- No, I'm not annoyed.
- You look annoyed.

15:57.165 --> 15:59.375
What about everybody who died before me?
Where's my parents?

15:59.376 --> 16:00.626
How do I see them?

16:00.627 --> 16:04.421
You could definitely go see your parents.
But then, you know, you'd be…

16:04.422 --> 16:06.800
- Be with my parents for eternity.
- Eternity.

16:08.009 --> 16:10.762
That's why we usually recommend
for you to do you.

16:11.721 --> 16:14.390
And just know that everyone
is existing pretty damn good.

16:14.391 --> 16:15.558
You know what I mean?

16:19.688 --> 16:22.231
You know, Joan always thought of death

16:22.232 --> 16:25.025
as one more surprise
waiting around the corner.

16:25.026 --> 16:26.860
- Mmm.
- And she loved surprises.

16:26.861 --> 16:28.487
But she was a librarian though, right?

16:28.488 --> 16:30.239
Yeah, they can like surprises too.

16:30.240 --> 16:31.241
Oh.

16:32.742 --> 16:34.785
So if I wanted to wait,
what do I have to do?

16:34.786 --> 16:36.370
Get a job? Be a bartender?

16:36.371 --> 16:39.373
No. You wish.
It's cleaning work.

16:39.374 --> 16:41.584
- Do you know how to do laundry?
- Yeah.

16:43.920 --> 16:45.171
At least the room is nice.

16:46.089 --> 16:49.216
Yeah. But it's for clients.

16:49.217 --> 16:52.177
So if you don't decide,
then you have to go…

16:52.178 --> 16:53.595
Well, I was told there is no hell.

16:53.596 --> 16:56.098
- The basement.
- Oh.

16:56.099 --> 16:58.225
The rooms are more functional
in the basement.

16:58.226 --> 17:00.437
- Mmm.
- Jesus, you went straight to hell.

17:02.522 --> 17:04.648
You look like you hate people.
Try Hermit World.

17:04.649 --> 17:06.776
Hi. Excuse me…

17:07.777 --> 17:09.863
Do you want a little sniffle? And you?

17:17.036 --> 17:20.874
Final call for Cowboy World 167.

17:27.130 --> 17:28.131
Smoke, sir?

17:31.676 --> 17:33.051
It could be tomorrow.

17:33.052 --> 17:36.388
Or she could hang on for another,
what, six or seven months?

17:36.389 --> 17:38.974
I mean, I guess I could
set everything up for her.

17:38.975 --> 17:42.102
And I could, you know, make sure
it's… it's how she likes it,

17:42.103 --> 17:43.855
really make it feel like a home.

17:44.439 --> 17:46.274
Larry, that is so romantic.

17:47.984 --> 17:50.527
- I guess it is a little romantic.
- It's so romantic.

17:50.528 --> 17:53.071
- I can be romantic.
- I…

17:53.072 --> 17:55.658
- 'Cause I know how she likes things.
- You do.

18:43.122 --> 18:44.206
Oh.

18:44.207 --> 18:47.292
I really think you picked a good one.
You are not going to regret this, Larry.

18:47.293 --> 18:50.129
- Hey, hey, uh, would you do me a favor?
- Yeah, sure can do.

18:50.839 --> 18:52.256
Could you give Joan this letter for me?

18:52.257 --> 18:54.132
No can do. That's against the rules.

18:54.133 --> 18:56.134
Plus, why do you need a letter
when you got me?

18:56.135 --> 18:59.847
Beach Land 239,
now boarding at gate 12.

18:59.848 --> 19:01.598
It was a pleasure working with you.

19:01.599 --> 19:02.600
Yeah.

19:07.021 --> 19:08.022
Bye.

19:09.399 --> 19:10.608
Bye.

19:13.152 --> 19:14.863
Sorry. Oh.

19:16.072 --> 19:17.073
Ow.

19:19.909 --> 19:20.910
Shoot.

19:21.411 --> 19:22.412
Okay.

19:30.587 --> 19:34.549
Mind your step.
Disorientation is normal.

19:41.639 --> 19:42.890
Joan.

19:42.891 --> 19:44.100
Joan!

19:44.851 --> 19:46.351
Joan! Joan!

19:46.352 --> 19:48.562
That's my wife.

19:48.563 --> 19:49.898
Yeah. Come on, buddy.

19:51.065 --> 19:52.859
- It's that way.
- Yeah, okay. Yeah, yeah.

19:54.986 --> 19:57.280
Come on, come on, come on, come on!
Come on.

19:58.948 --> 20:00.032
There you go.

20:00.033 --> 20:04.746
The newly dead from
North America, arriving in Junction 301.

20:07.081 --> 20:10.167
Oh, excuse me. Excuse me.
Sorry, where am I?

20:10.168 --> 20:12.377
Um, your AC will explain everything.

20:12.378 --> 20:15.088
Okay. Okay.
You know, it's just…

20:15.089 --> 20:18.009
Honey, your AC will explain everything.

20:23.181 --> 20:24.390
That looks nice.

20:24.891 --> 20:27.601
Joan. Joan! Joan.

20:27.602 --> 20:28.977
- Larry!
- Joan.

20:28.978 --> 20:32.230
- Sweetie. Ah, sweetie.
- Oh, my God.

20:32.231 --> 20:33.440
I missed you so much.

20:33.441 --> 20:37.194
- Hi. Oh. Oh, my God.
- Wow, look at you. Wow. I love this.

20:37.195 --> 20:41.281
I was, uh, I was in bed, and then I…
I thought I just came from a…

20:41.282 --> 20:42.699
- Baby, you look amazing.
- …a-a train.

20:42.700 --> 20:44.952
- Oh! Every time!
- Ow! Ow!

20:44.953 --> 20:48.747
God, every damn time, Larry.
I told you to slow down on the pretzels.

20:48.748 --> 20:50.791
- But, you… No, no, you never listen.
- I know, I know.

20:50.792 --> 20:52.167
Oh, you stop smiling.

20:52.168 --> 20:53.251
- Jo?
- Yeah.

20:53.252 --> 20:55.128
Listen to me, honey. I have shocking news.

20:55.129 --> 20:56.130
- You're dead.
- I'm dead.

20:56.714 --> 20:58.090
Yeah. How'd you know?

20:58.091 --> 20:59.174
I mean…

20:59.175 --> 21:01.635
It took him forever to figure that out.

21:01.636 --> 21:03.345
- Not forever.
- Yeah, forever.

21:03.346 --> 21:06.515
- No.
- So you are the famous Joan.

21:06.516 --> 21:09.476
Okay, Larry. Way to marry up.

21:09.477 --> 21:12.479
- Yeah.
- So, uh, what-what now?

21:12.480 --> 21:13.563
Yeah, so now, so--

21:13.564 --> 21:14.774
Was it cancer?

21:15.900 --> 21:17.819
That took you away from the world?

21:18.528 --> 21:19.778
So, who are you?

21:19.779 --> 21:23.031
Okay, honey. So listen,
now we finally get to have that holiday.

21:23.032 --> 21:25.450
And basically we can go
anywhere we want, but then that's it.

21:25.451 --> 21:28.036
It's like a one and done thing here.
They're very strict on that.

21:28.037 --> 21:29.997
Um, and if you want to go
to the mountains we can,

21:29.998 --> 21:33.375
because the snow and the cold's not
gonna kill you now, 'cause you're dead.

21:33.376 --> 21:35.293
- Back away from my client.
- I'm not near your client.

21:35.294 --> 21:36.545
- Back away.
- Shut up.

21:36.546 --> 21:38.755
I've been waiting for this golden goose
for 67 goddamn years.

21:38.756 --> 21:39.840
- Oh, Lar?
- Hi.

21:39.841 --> 21:42.092
- Excuse me. Excuse me.
- I'm so sorry about her.

21:42.093 --> 21:43.176
Who's that?

21:43.177 --> 21:45.554
I'm Ryan.
I'm your afterlife coordinator.

21:45.555 --> 21:46.638
Yeah.

21:46.639 --> 21:48.807
I know this can be
very, very overwhelming.

21:48.808 --> 21:50.809
It's a lot to absorb,
so I highly recommend just…

21:50.810 --> 21:55.230
…taking a deep breath in,
and… [exhales deeply] …out.

21:55.231 --> 21:57.191
Just breathe out.

22:31.142 --> 22:32.726
Oh. Hey. What's going on, guy?

22:32.727 --> 22:34.478
This was my, uh, bartender.

22:34.479 --> 22:37.689
I, um, guess I forgot to pay the tab.
I didn't realize there would be a tab.

22:37.690 --> 22:38.941
Nobody gave me any money.

22:39.984 --> 22:42.861
No way.

22:42.862 --> 22:44.780
Sorry. I forgot to ask your name.
What's your name again?

22:44.781 --> 22:46.281
I'm Luke.

22:46.282 --> 22:47.825
This is Luke. He's my bartender.

22:49.118 --> 22:50.453
Joan.

22:51.120 --> 22:52.330
Oh, no.

22:53.998 --> 22:56.542
I never dreamt you this clearly.

22:57.960 --> 23:00.003
You're exactly how I dreamt you.

23:00.004 --> 23:02.048
Oof. Hard luck, Larry.

23:03.716 --> 23:05.842
No. Luke had a mustache.

23:05.843 --> 23:07.552
Yeah, well, Joanie hated it.

23:07.553 --> 23:10.514
So I shave it off every morning
hoping she's gonna show up.

23:10.515 --> 23:13.392
- Oh, my God.
- How romantic.

23:16.270 --> 23:17.313
And you did.

23:19.065 --> 23:20.108
Okay, sweetie.

23:21.734 --> 23:22.818
- Okay.
- Oh.

23:22.819 --> 23:24.319
- What you doing?
- Larry?

23:24.320 --> 23:25.821
- Okay, sweetie.
- I…

23:25.822 --> 23:27.030
- Let's go.
- Oh.

23:27.031 --> 23:28.615
- Who's this guy?
- The second husband.

23:28.616 --> 23:31.368
- I prefer current husband.
- The current husband.

23:31.369 --> 23:34.330
- Oh.
- Joanie, you're all right?

23:34.997 --> 23:36.081
Oh, my God.

23:36.082 --> 23:38.792
Honey. It was a lot for me too.

23:38.793 --> 23:42.587
Okay. I have to insist that I explain
exactly what's going on to my client.

23:42.588 --> 23:48.301
She clearly has
a very "difficult" decision to make.

23:48.302 --> 23:50.887
- Okay. Oh, that…
- Come on.

23:50.888 --> 23:53.933
- Oh, my God, he's really here.
- And very attractive.

23:54.934 --> 23:56.017
Is he taller?

23:56.018 --> 23:58.020
So when you said you were waiting…

23:58.604 --> 24:01.107
I conjured her image every day in my mind.

24:02.066 --> 24:06.821
Thought I did a good job,
but she's more stunning than I remember.

24:07.530 --> 24:09.991
Okay. That's a line, Luke.

24:10.908 --> 24:12.326
You were my bartender.

24:14.662 --> 24:15.745
Hmm?

24:15.746 --> 24:19.167
Nope. Nope. Nope.

24:20.585 --> 24:22.420
- Uh, mmm no.
- God, he looked so young.

24:23.254 --> 24:24.796
This will have to do.

24:24.797 --> 24:26.757
Was he always that young?

24:27.300 --> 24:28.717
That's a lot to take in.

24:28.718 --> 24:32.179
The love of your life waiting 67 years.

24:32.180 --> 24:33.555
And Larry.

24:33.556 --> 24:35.223
Larry is my husband.

24:35.224 --> 24:37.225
- One of two.
- Yeah.

24:37.226 --> 24:38.310
Oh, that's pretty.

24:38.311 --> 24:41.646
You'll feel much better after you change
out of that morbid ensemble.

24:41.647 --> 24:44.858
Ah. Oh. Oh.

24:44.859 --> 24:46.318
Yeah, that's pretty.

24:46.319 --> 24:48.279
That's… Oh, he's so young.

24:49.155 --> 24:51.364
Oh, he's so young. Oh, I don't…

24:51.365 --> 24:52.908
What's your ETA, doll?

24:52.909 --> 24:55.703
- Oh.
- How's it looking?

24:57.747 --> 24:59.456
So… What…

24:59.457 --> 25:01.083
What am I supposed to do, huh?

25:01.584 --> 25:04.336
I need you to tell me…
…what to do.

25:04.337 --> 25:06.881
Oh, my dear. Okay. I read your file.

25:07.465 --> 25:10.300
And you are smart,
passionate and decisive.

25:10.301 --> 25:11.761
Oh. I am?

25:12.428 --> 25:16.056
I have complete faith that you
will choose the right eternity…

25:16.057 --> 25:19.142
- Yeah.
- …and the right person to spend it with.

25:19.143 --> 25:20.769
- Mmm.
- You'll do.

25:20.770 --> 25:23.105
Do for what?

25:24.315 --> 25:25.815
Were you expecting someone, or…

25:25.816 --> 25:27.109
Were you?

25:28.027 --> 25:30.528
Uh…

25:30.529 --> 25:33.991
Oh, my God, Luke.
What a surprise.

25:34.659 --> 25:36.201
What the hell, Reese?

25:36.202 --> 25:39.162
It's Ryan,
and it's been Ryan for the last half hour.

25:39.163 --> 25:41.957
- Yeah.
- You look amazing.

25:41.958 --> 25:44.084
Yeah. I'm married.

25:44.085 --> 25:45.961
- To him.
- To Larry.

25:45.962 --> 25:47.879
And Larry seems nice.

25:47.880 --> 25:52.092
Look, Joan, you must have thought,
or hoped, that this might happen?

25:52.093 --> 25:56.471
Well, I mean, yeah. Yeah, yeah.
You know, I-I have imagined it.

25:56.472 --> 25:57.890
Great.

25:58.599 --> 26:00.016
Hi.

26:00.017 --> 26:02.185
- I'll leave you kids to it.
- Oh.

26:02.186 --> 26:03.271
Hi.

26:05.481 --> 26:07.482
Did you even read my file?

26:07.483 --> 26:10.068
You're more than words on a page
to me, buddy. You didn't even bring it up.

26:10.069 --> 26:12.195
Yeah, well, I had a lot on my mind.
I just died.

26:12.196 --> 26:16.241
So, I'm sorry that I forgot to mention
that my wife's ex might be hanging around.

26:16.242 --> 26:18.076
Technically,
I don't think we can call him her ex.

26:18.077 --> 26:19.703
First husband, maybe, but not an ex.

26:19.704 --> 26:21.788
No, I'm not calling…
I'm never calling him that.

26:21.789 --> 26:25.041
Okay. I'm just trying to anticipate
what Ryan's gonna say. We have history.

26:25.042 --> 26:26.334
Great. What kind of history?

26:26.335 --> 26:29.087
- It was sexual.
- Of course it was.

26:29.088 --> 26:32.173
You know how many people wanted this case?
So many people.

26:32.174 --> 26:33.258
Really?

26:33.259 --> 26:36.011
A man that's waited half a century
for his love? Ah!

26:36.012 --> 26:37.470
That's kinda sad if you think about it.

26:37.471 --> 26:39.473
You really think that's the way
that Joan's gonna think about it?

26:40.141 --> 26:41.975
- I don't know.
- It's okay.

26:41.976 --> 26:43.768
I'm sure they've had one of these before.

26:43.769 --> 26:45.687
I mean, I don't know about it.
I've never had it.

26:45.688 --> 26:48.023
But I bet you there's a process.

26:48.024 --> 26:50.318
- He looks like Montgomery Clift.
- Oof!

26:50.860 --> 26:53.278
Oh, my gosh,
I was saying this just the other day.

26:53.279 --> 26:56.239
Montgomery Clift. He is so handsome.

26:56.240 --> 26:58.700
- Luke is so handsome.
- You're not helping.

26:58.701 --> 27:01.703
I'm sorry, but it is what it is.

27:01.704 --> 27:02.996
Luke is hot.

27:02.997 --> 27:06.207
His eyes are bluer than the ocean.
He has a better narrative.

27:06.208 --> 27:07.459
No, he doesn't.

27:07.460 --> 27:08.835
I have a better narrative.

27:08.836 --> 27:11.755
I was married to her for 65 years
and I gave her children.

27:11.756 --> 27:14.591
Exactly. We go with that. That's strong.

27:14.592 --> 27:16.801
There's nothing more powerful
than emotional blackmail.

27:16.802 --> 27:18.094
- Right?
- Good on ya.

27:21.182 --> 27:24.101
So… …how have you been?

27:25.227 --> 27:26.854
Good. Yeah.

27:27.646 --> 27:31.359
Well, I mean, I've been obviously dead,
but, you know, good.

27:32.610 --> 27:34.861
- Well, you look good.
- Yeah.

27:34.862 --> 27:36.821
I mean, you know, you always…
you always looked…

27:36.822 --> 27:40.158
- You always looked good.
- Oh, yeah. Coming from you, huh?

27:40.159 --> 27:42.119
Oh. Oh.

27:46.082 --> 27:47.333
Oh.

27:50.044 --> 27:51.128
Yeah, I, uh…

27:54.090 --> 27:57.801
Look. I-I don't know what to say.
It's…

27:57.802 --> 28:00.178
Well, I had a long time
to think about what I was going to say.

28:00.179 --> 28:02.473
- Oh.
- I mean, I had a long, long time.

28:02.973 --> 28:03.933
And?

28:04.725 --> 28:06.685
And I'm drawing a blank.

28:07.228 --> 28:08.520
Oh.

28:08.521 --> 28:10.480
Warning. Code seven four.

28:10.481 --> 28:11.940
- Code seven four.
- Oh! Oh.

28:11.941 --> 28:13.525
- Eyes on the bogey.
- What the hell?

28:13.526 --> 28:15.151
Gary.

28:15.152 --> 28:17.195
Hey, Luke. You working tonight?

28:17.196 --> 28:18.780
Not tonight. Tonight's a night off.

28:18.781 --> 28:21.075
Wait. Is this…

28:21.659 --> 28:22.909
Mm-hmm.

28:22.910 --> 28:25.871
Joan? No!

28:26.831 --> 28:29.040
- No. No, please.
- Move it!

28:29.041 --> 28:31.418
I can't look at
another goddamn painting.

28:31.419 --> 28:32.794
- It's so boring.
- All right.

28:32.795 --> 28:34.212
- Well, I better go.
- No!

28:34.213 --> 28:36.214
- But, hey, you are one lucky lady.
- Hmm?

28:36.215 --> 28:37.298
Gary!

28:37.299 --> 28:38.466
- Oh.
- Huh.

28:38.467 --> 28:40.468
- Move it. I'm sick of this crap.
- No, please!

28:40.469 --> 28:41.970
Get in here now!

28:41.971 --> 28:43.138
Oof.

28:43.139 --> 28:44.681
Museum World's the worst!

28:44.682 --> 28:46.142
Oh, God.

28:47.268 --> 28:50.562
Oh, my God.
What-What did he do?

28:50.563 --> 28:52.565
Oh, he tried to escape his eternity.

28:53.607 --> 28:55.651
Once you've chosen,
you can't go back here.

28:56.152 --> 28:57.361
You have to get it right.

28:58.195 --> 29:00.780
- Oh, that's a lot of pressure.
- Yeah, it is.

29:00.781 --> 29:03.909
Look. I remembered
what I wanted to say to you first.

29:04.535 --> 29:05.536
What?

29:06.704 --> 29:07.746
I love you.

29:10.124 --> 29:11.125
Oh.

29:11.792 --> 29:14.461
That's a… That's a good opener.

29:14.462 --> 29:15.463
Yeah.

29:16.172 --> 29:19.717
Look, I know this is hard for you,
but I missed you.

29:21.177 --> 29:22.970
I thought about you every single day.

29:23.471 --> 29:26.724
There wasn't a day that went by
that I didn't think of you.

29:28.309 --> 29:31.145
Yeah. You know, I…

29:31.729 --> 29:33.230
I wanted you to be happy.

29:33.939 --> 29:35.608
I wanted you to have a life.

29:36.984 --> 29:38.777
- Yeah?
- Yeah, of course.

29:39.987 --> 29:41.446
But I waited.

29:41.447 --> 29:46.451
You know, I-I waited because I wanted us
to have a chance to have one too.

29:46.452 --> 29:48.204
Oh.

29:49.705 --> 29:50.788
I'm gonna be sick.

29:50.789 --> 29:52.624
- You okay?
- Oh, God. Why can you get sick here?

29:52.625 --> 29:54.709
- Joan.
- Oh.

29:54.710 --> 29:56.503
- You all right?
- Uh, Luke? Luke, please.

29:56.504 --> 29:57.879
I need to think.

29:57.880 --> 30:00.049
Okay?

30:11.644 --> 30:12.645
Oh.

30:13.437 --> 30:14.438
Okay.

30:25.282 --> 30:26.283
Luke?

30:27.159 --> 30:28.160
Oh.

30:29.828 --> 30:31.830
Okay.

30:38.212 --> 30:39.504
- Hey, sweetie.
- Oh, Larry.

30:39.505 --> 30:42.799
So, I know this is a lot, but don't worry.
I've been doing the research.

30:42.800 --> 30:44.801
And here are some pretty good options.

30:44.802 --> 30:45.927
Sorry, options for?

30:45.928 --> 30:47.179
Yeah, for our eternity.

30:47.763 --> 30:49.222
What?

30:49.223 --> 30:52.058
Wow. You really look amazing.

30:52.059 --> 30:54.185
- The long hair suits you. I love it.
- Oh.

30:54.186 --> 30:55.478
What?

30:55.479 --> 30:57.523
Oh. Everything works here.

30:58.107 --> 30:59.649
Oh, Larry.

30:59.650 --> 31:02.151
- What do you mean, "Larry"?
- Well, it's complicated.

31:02.152 --> 31:03.403
We were together a week ago.

31:03.404 --> 31:07.240
Yeah, well, a lot has happened in a week.
You died, Karen died. I died.

31:07.241 --> 31:10.618
I just been reunited
with both of my dead husbands.

31:10.619 --> 31:13.663
And I learned that I have only a week
to pick where to spend eternity.

31:13.664 --> 31:16.541
Karen finally kicked it.
It's a big week for Oakdale.

31:16.542 --> 31:17.543
Oh.

31:18.210 --> 31:19.669
Oh.

31:19.670 --> 31:20.671
Hey.

31:21.839 --> 31:24.382
- I know what'll make you feel better.
- Oh, what?

31:24.383 --> 31:25.508
Squatting.

31:25.509 --> 31:27.051
Oh, Jesus Christ.

31:27.052 --> 31:28.345
Just try it.

31:29.471 --> 31:30.972
- Fine. Okay.
- I'm telling you.

31:30.973 --> 31:32.140
- Come on. Go.
- Okay, fine.

31:33.225 --> 31:34.226
Go.

31:36.020 --> 31:37.021
Yeah.

31:37.521 --> 31:39.106
- Wow.
- I know, right?

31:39.690 --> 31:42.191
- I got so low there.
- You did get so low there.

31:42.192 --> 31:44.569
Yeah. I know. It feels so good.

31:45.988 --> 31:47.363
I've been doing a bunch of stuff.

31:47.364 --> 31:49.324
- Oh. Looking good.
- Yeah.

31:49.325 --> 31:51.868
- You look good.
- I know. Thanks. Thanks.

31:51.869 --> 31:54.037
- Work it out.
- I miss these hips.

31:54.038 --> 31:55.913
- Whoo!
- Oh, God.

31:55.914 --> 31:57.958
Yeah, look at this. Look at this.

31:59.918 --> 32:04.589
Oh. You were right.
That, uh, that did make me feel better.

32:04.590 --> 32:05.757
I knew it would.

32:05.758 --> 32:07.842
Oh.

32:10.846 --> 32:12.430
Are you kidding me?

32:12.431 --> 32:14.182
- Larry!
- It's too much salt.

32:15.476 --> 32:16.852
I need… I need time.

32:17.436 --> 32:19.104
Okay? I…

32:20.314 --> 32:22.190
I just… I need to clear my head.

32:22.191 --> 32:25.277
Okay. You're right. I'm being insensitive.

32:26.362 --> 32:28.072
And we can talk about it in the morning.

32:28.572 --> 32:29.990
- Thank you.
- Okay.

32:42.628 --> 32:44.420
- These are so stupid.
- Are you kidding me?

32:44.421 --> 32:45.755
What are you doing?

32:45.756 --> 32:47.006
I'm going to bed.

32:47.007 --> 32:48.342
I'm tired too.

32:49.134 --> 32:50.177
Long day for me.

33:01.313 --> 33:02.314
Oh.

33:05.859 --> 33:07.194
Oh, Larry.

33:10.197 --> 33:11.198
Oh.

33:17.329 --> 33:21.833
Remember,
geopolitical differences no longer matter.

33:21.834 --> 33:22.876
You are dead.

33:24.086 --> 33:26.714
Sorry, buddy, but your seven days are up.

33:37.015 --> 33:38.141
Holy crap.

33:38.142 --> 33:41.811
"Holy crap. For God's sakes. Bloody hell."
Are you sure you're not religious?

33:41.812 --> 33:42.979
Hey, hey, hey. Is he here?

33:42.980 --> 33:45.440
Oh, yeah, he is. But it's sad actually.

33:45.441 --> 33:47.609
No, he's… He-He's my Jo's favorite.

33:48.277 --> 33:49.902
- Him?
- Yeah. She loves him.

33:49.903 --> 33:51.155
- Really?
- He's the best.

33:51.822 --> 33:52.947
Oh, okay.

33:52.948 --> 33:54.073
Hey, do you know him?

33:54.074 --> 33:55.491
Yeah, of course I know him.

33:55.492 --> 33:56.909
Would he do you a favor?

33:56.910 --> 33:59.746
Who you talking to?
It's me. Obviously, duh.

33:59.747 --> 34:01.456
- But you're sure? Him?
- Yes.

34:01.457 --> 34:02.499
Okay.

34:03.083 --> 34:06.003
Wow. Look at this.

34:06.587 --> 34:08.839
Single bed. That's nice, right?

34:09.339 --> 34:12.216
We got ourselves here a kitchenette.

34:12.217 --> 34:13.426
Handy.

34:13.427 --> 34:15.178
Let's see what's in that fridge.

34:15.179 --> 34:16.305
Oh, my gosh.

34:17.556 --> 34:19.056
You are in luck.

34:19.057 --> 34:20.141
Hummus.

34:20.142 --> 34:21.435
You know what? It's fine.

34:21.935 --> 34:24.604
You sort this out for me,
I'll be outta here in no time.

34:24.605 --> 34:26.189
- Oh, I love it.
- This is gonna save it.

34:26.190 --> 34:27.607
I love it. You are focused.

34:27.608 --> 34:29.692
- Keeping your eyes on the prize.
- What's that smell?

34:29.693 --> 34:31.695
- It's hummus.
- No, it's not.

34:50.047 --> 34:51.297
I…

35:02.893 --> 35:03.976
All right.

35:03.977 --> 35:09.941
Ever think 1930s Germany would've
been great if it wasn't for all the Nazis?

35:11.193 --> 35:12.569
Well, think no more.

35:18.951 --> 35:20.160
Oh.

35:20.911 --> 35:22.037
Please be coffee.

35:23.372 --> 35:25.457
Okay. Please be coffee.

35:26.041 --> 35:28.000
Oh, Larry.

35:28.001 --> 35:29.627
I know, I know,
but I got a surprise for you.

35:29.628 --> 35:32.797
No, no, no.
I actually need less surprises.

35:32.798 --> 35:35.174
Like, just, you know, zero surprises.

35:35.175 --> 35:37.301
Joan, I promise you're gonna like this.

35:37.302 --> 35:38.303
You trust me, right?

35:39.555 --> 35:40.806
Yeah. Okay.

35:41.890 --> 35:42.891
Yeah.

35:44.142 --> 35:45.143
She trusts me.

35:47.187 --> 35:49.981
Next arrival in 15 minutes.

35:49.982 --> 35:51.816
You look incredible.

35:51.817 --> 35:53.359
- Thanks, honey.
- Yeah.

35:53.360 --> 35:54.403
Are you excited?

35:55.279 --> 35:57.698
- Sure.
- Got any ideas what it could be?

35:58.198 --> 35:59.366
No.

35:59.908 --> 36:01.951
- Here we go. Yeah.
- Oh, that's sweet. Look at you.

36:01.952 --> 36:02.953
That's for you.

36:03.912 --> 36:05.330
Need a little bubbles.

36:05.914 --> 36:07.373
Oh. That's, um…

36:07.374 --> 36:08.499
Yeah, that's sweet.

36:08.500 --> 36:10.084
What? Oh, no. That's not it.

36:10.085 --> 36:11.168
Oh, gosh.

36:11.169 --> 36:12.379
Lights!

36:16.300 --> 36:18.009
Look.
Look. Look up there.

36:18.010 --> 36:20.178
- Hon, is that… Wait, Larry.
- Yeah.

36:20.929 --> 36:25.182
♪ Everybody loves somebody sometime ♪

36:25.183 --> 36:27.643
- What'd I tell you? What'd I tell you?
- Oh, my God!

36:27.644 --> 36:29.854
That's our guy.

36:29.855 --> 36:31.397
♪ Everybody falls in love somehow ♪

36:31.398 --> 36:32.732
- I know.
- Oh, my goodness.

36:32.733 --> 36:34.901
- This is for Joan.
- Did I do good or what?

36:34.902 --> 36:38.029
- You really did. You did great.
- What did I tell ya?

36:38.030 --> 36:39.281
He sounds amazing.

36:39.990 --> 36:41.073
♪ My time… ♪

36:41.074 --> 36:43.451
- Ah, he looks great.
- Oh, my gosh. He really does.

36:43.452 --> 36:45.411
♪ …is now ♪

36:45.412 --> 36:46.914
Oh, okay.

36:47.456 --> 36:49.624
- Guess he still likes to drink.
- Yeah.

36:49.625 --> 36:52.543
- Or he's just, you know, a little rusty.
- Yeah.

36:52.544 --> 36:53.920
- Still for Jill.
- Joan!

36:53.921 --> 36:56.131
♪ Falls in love somehow ♪

36:58.258 --> 37:01.052
♪ Something in my heart keeps saying ♪

37:01.053 --> 37:02.429
Keep it together.

37:03.013 --> 37:05.556
- Larry, are you sure that's Dean Martin?
- I don't know.

37:06.642 --> 37:08.517
♪ …is here ♪

37:08.518 --> 37:10.187
Oh, shit.

37:11.063 --> 37:12.314
- Be right back.
- Okay.

37:16.276 --> 37:18.569
Anna, who the hell is this?
That's not Dean Martin.

37:18.570 --> 37:21.280
- Hey, baby.
- Of course not. It's Richard Johnson.

37:21.281 --> 37:24.116
- Oh, no. No.
- Celebrity impersonators die too, Larry.

37:24.117 --> 37:26.243
- Why wouldn't you tell me?
- I thought you knew.

37:26.244 --> 37:28.746
I thought it was weird you kept saying,
"This is Joanie's favorite."

37:28.747 --> 37:31.165
I was like, "Richard?
Richard is Joanie's favorite?"

37:31.166 --> 37:32.583
You knew that's not what I meant.

37:32.584 --> 37:35.878
Well, now that I say it out loud,
I understand that it does not make sense.

37:35.879 --> 37:38.214
- Please. I'm so lonely, babe.
- Oh.

37:38.215 --> 37:42.259
Also, he has a crippling alcohol problem,
and I forgot to mention that to you,

37:42.260 --> 37:43.719
and that's my bad.

37:43.720 --> 37:46.138
- That is your bad.
- Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

37:46.139 --> 37:49.725
I can't fathom a scenario
which this could've gone worse.

37:49.726 --> 37:52.144
Help Ol' Blue Eyes
with his old blue balls, huh?

37:52.145 --> 37:53.730
- No, no, no.
- Oh, my…

37:54.398 --> 37:55.648
Oh. Hey, Luke.

37:57.359 --> 37:59.361
- Blue Eyes was Frank.
- You're the man, Luke!

37:59.945 --> 38:03.114
- It just got worse. It just got worse.
- Oh.

38:03.115 --> 38:04.782
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

38:04.783 --> 38:06.826
- Yeah?
- Yeah, thanks. Sorry.

38:06.827 --> 38:08.244
I'm grateful that you were passing.

38:08.245 --> 38:09.787
Well, actually, I was… Um…

38:09.788 --> 38:11.747
- You were… No. Oh, no.
- Well, I was here because…

38:11.748 --> 38:13.332
Luke, take her back to the room
for a hot bath.

38:13.333 --> 38:14.583
Okay, yeah. I think we got it--

38:16.461 --> 38:18.796
I don't know what that guy was doing.
And why are you going--

38:18.797 --> 38:20.381
- What is wrong with you?
- I know. I'm trying.

38:20.382 --> 38:22.091
I thought it was the real Dean Martin.
I swear to God.

38:22.092 --> 38:24.344
- What's your problem?
- Stop! Stop it!

38:28.807 --> 38:29.933
You two, come with me.

38:30.642 --> 38:32.518
No. No, no, no, no, no, no.

38:32.519 --> 38:34.688
You two st… You stay here.

38:36.440 --> 38:38.315
Excuse me, y'all. Excuse me.

38:38.316 --> 38:40.192
Excuse me.

38:40.193 --> 38:41.278
You're excused.

38:43.238 --> 38:44.989
You know, I could've handled that myself.

38:44.990 --> 38:46.033
Yeah.

38:47.159 --> 38:48.160
Yeah.

38:49.202 --> 38:51.746
Yeah. Yeah.

38:51.747 --> 38:55.875
You know, my grandfather,
he had psychotic issues.

38:55.876 --> 39:00.547
And maybe it just skips a generation.
Because there's no way that this is real.

39:01.423 --> 39:05.802
How in God's name can this be real?
My God.

39:07.471 --> 39:08.472
Is this hell?

39:09.639 --> 39:11.016
Is this hell?

39:11.600 --> 39:13.769
- Technically, hell does--
- No, no! I didn't say speak.

39:17.481 --> 39:20.066
You ever work this place out?

39:20.067 --> 39:23.527
Nah. It just gets more and more confusing.

39:23.528 --> 39:27.490
Do not be alarmed.
Everything is as it should be.

39:27.491 --> 39:29.241
Gimme your phone. Just give it to me.

39:29.242 --> 39:32.870
Hey, honey. So we're talking
about bending the rules just a smidge.

39:32.871 --> 39:35.164
- It was my idea.
- It was my idea.

39:35.165 --> 39:39.043
I took his idea
and I made it better. I'm making a plan.

39:39.044 --> 39:40.503
Oh, it's about control?

39:40.504 --> 39:41.922
Yep. Yep.

39:55.060 --> 39:56.061
Oh.

40:06.655 --> 40:08.531
- So?
- Good news.

40:08.532 --> 40:11.158
- I talked to Frank, and basically--
- Actually, I talked to Frank.

40:11.159 --> 40:12.952
The point is, somebody talked to Frank.

40:12.953 --> 40:16.705
They then talked to Tom,
and then they talked to a guy way up top.

40:16.706 --> 40:18.375
- The big guy.
- Kevin.

40:18.875 --> 40:20.543
And you got approved for a plan.

40:20.544 --> 40:21.794
Anna, just say the plan.

40:21.795 --> 40:23.671
- Okay, sorry. So typic--
- So, typically here--

40:23.672 --> 40:24.881
Anna. You're Anna?

40:25.465 --> 40:26.633
- No.
- Okay.

40:27.175 --> 40:28.467
So typically when you get here,

40:28.468 --> 40:30.761
you get to pick eternity,
and that's it. Bing, bang, boom.

40:30.762 --> 40:35.766
However, in this unique circumstance,
you've gotten approved for a special visa.

40:35.767 --> 40:38.144
Joan will be allowed
two visits to an eternity.

40:38.145 --> 40:40.271
- One with each of her former husbands.
- Mm-hmm.

40:40.272 --> 40:42.524
- And then?
- And then she'll decide.

40:43.692 --> 40:44.859
Between the two of you.

40:44.860 --> 40:47.111
It seems like kind
of a high-pressure scenario.

40:47.112 --> 40:49.446
Okay. Well, you could all
choose the same eternity

40:49.447 --> 40:50.614
and then work it out from there.

40:50.615 --> 40:52.825
But then you'd be
in the same place together forever.

40:52.826 --> 40:54.118
Oh, that could work.

40:54.119 --> 40:55.411
- No, no.
- I'm done…

40:55.412 --> 40:57.163
I'm done with this guy creeping
in the shadows.

40:57.164 --> 40:58.831
- Creeping in the shadows?
- Lurking.

40:58.832 --> 41:00.708
- Lurking?
- Yeah. You're a lurker, pal.

41:00.709 --> 41:03.502
And you're waiting beyond to spoil
a half a century of marriage.

41:03.503 --> 41:05.254
Well, I'm sorry
I died defending our country.

41:05.255 --> 41:07.673
- It was Korea, buddy. Relax.
- What'd you say to me?

41:07.674 --> 41:09.885
You didn't exactly storm the beaches
of Normandy, did you?

41:11.469 --> 41:13.512
- What… What are you doing?
- You went there.

41:13.513 --> 41:15.014
Hey. Hey! Stop!

41:15.015 --> 41:16.140
- Hit him back, Larry.
- Stop!

41:16.141 --> 41:17.933
- I will bare-knuckle you.
- Yes, Luke!

41:17.934 --> 41:19.185
Stop it! Okay?

41:19.186 --> 41:20.937
This is what we're doing!

41:21.521 --> 41:23.773
So, just…

41:25.692 --> 41:28.068
flip a coin and decide who's going first.

41:28.069 --> 41:29.278
No.

41:29.279 --> 41:32.198
I will not stand for another man
dating my wife.

41:33.116 --> 41:35.868
Maybe you should've thought about that
before you married another man's wife.

41:35.869 --> 41:36.870
Boys!

41:37.954 --> 41:39.206
Who's going first?

41:41.666 --> 41:43.210
I have a coin.

41:50.258 --> 41:51.508
Oh, shit.

41:51.509 --> 41:53.928
- Is that a pretzel?
- No.

41:53.929 --> 41:55.554
- Oh, my God.
- You still eating pretzels.

41:55.555 --> 41:57.390
- Yeah. Relax.
- Get on with it.

41:58.475 --> 41:59.476
Heads or tails?

42:00.060 --> 42:01.061
Heads.

42:02.062 --> 42:05.564
The next stop
is Mountain World 312.

42:05.565 --> 42:06.566
Oh.

42:10.862 --> 42:12.197
- What?
- I just…

42:13.740 --> 42:15.408
forgot how handsome you are.

42:15.909 --> 42:18.202
We were an attractive couple.

42:18.203 --> 42:20.413
Oh, come on. Everybody…

42:20.997 --> 42:24.709
Everybody assumed that
you got me pregnant and had to marry me.

42:25.252 --> 42:27.419
Yeah, no. My mother, she was…
she was so upset

42:27.420 --> 42:30.089
when I told her that I wasn't,
because she…

42:30.090 --> 42:32.634
Well, she wanted hot grandkids so badly.

42:33.260 --> 42:34.343
Not that my kids are ugly.

42:34.344 --> 42:36.054
I'm sure that they are hot.

42:37.514 --> 42:39.014
Not that I care.

42:39.015 --> 42:40.099
I didn't assume.

42:40.100 --> 42:42.559
Yeah. 'Cause I'm not…
I'm not into hot kids.

42:42.560 --> 42:44.521
No, I'm not into hot kids either.

42:46.523 --> 42:47.732
Yeah.

42:50.902 --> 42:52.195
I'm not into kids.

42:53.488 --> 42:54.489
Good.

42:55.156 --> 42:56.157
That's good.

43:17.304 --> 43:19.347
I remember the sky being bluer.

43:20.181 --> 43:21.182
Oh.

43:21.891 --> 43:23.101
Was it always that shade?

43:23.643 --> 43:24.769
Oh, yeah. Pretty much.

43:26.604 --> 43:28.063
Is that cloud moving?

43:30.358 --> 43:31.359
Yep.

43:33.403 --> 43:34.404
They move.

43:44.622 --> 43:46.166
Is it how you imagined it?

43:46.833 --> 43:47.917
It's perfect.

43:53.256 --> 43:55.050
Oh, boy. Oh. Okay.

43:56.092 --> 43:57.426
Okay.

44:00.305 --> 44:01.306
Can't die twice.

44:01.806 --> 44:03.265
You can't die twice.

44:03.266 --> 44:04.350
Okay.

44:12.692 --> 44:13.693
This okay?

44:15.570 --> 44:16.613
Mm-hmm.

44:17.113 --> 44:18.281
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

44:20.325 --> 44:23.285
No, we didn't know
where to put any of the trash.

44:23.286 --> 44:26.623
And so we didn't know they had a place
where bears didn't get to.

44:27.207 --> 44:29.459
It's cold. Was it always this cold?

44:30.794 --> 44:32.962
It's cold.

44:35.215 --> 44:37.467
Let's get you
somewhere nice and warm, huh?

44:38.093 --> 44:39.176
Mmm.

44:39.177 --> 44:42.221
I don't like how Luke's been going around
telling people he died in the war.

44:42.222 --> 44:43.847
Larry, the man died in the war.

44:43.848 --> 44:47.893
No, I know, but it's the way he says it.
"The war," like it's one of the cool ones.

44:47.894 --> 44:51.271
Okay, I think we should stop squabbling
about his obvious heroism,

44:51.272 --> 44:53.732
because I don't think
that's our strongest point of attack.

44:55.026 --> 44:58.112
The problem is
Luke's always been a memory.

44:58.113 --> 45:00.073
Now, I don't know
how you compete with a memory.

45:00.782 --> 45:03.575
All we are, are a collection of memories.

45:03.576 --> 45:05.619
That's depressing. I don't like that.

45:05.620 --> 45:07.955
But the point is, you're going
to have to remind her

45:07.956 --> 45:10.083
of why she fell in love with you
in the first place.

45:11.543 --> 45:12.544
Honestly…

45:14.254 --> 45:16.713
I don't know why she fell in love with me.

45:16.714 --> 45:17.715
Mmm.

45:18.508 --> 45:22.178
Well, you're gonna have
to figure that out. And fast.

45:27.225 --> 45:28.809
There's someone here I gotta find.

45:28.810 --> 45:31.855
Okay. Now we're cooking.
Now we're cooking.

45:34.899 --> 45:37.568
My great-granddaughter Charlotte
would love this place.

45:37.569 --> 45:39.237
She's a little adventurer.

45:40.029 --> 45:42.157
I guess so was her mother,
for that matter.

45:44.784 --> 45:46.703
- Sorry.
- It's fine.

45:48.246 --> 45:49.789
I'm sure she misses you.

45:50.748 --> 45:53.167
So is that okay? You know, talking about…

45:53.168 --> 45:56.462
- Mm-hmm. Yeah.
- Okay.

45:56.463 --> 45:58.338
- You're not angry with me?
- For what?

45:58.339 --> 46:00.966
It's just… Sixty-seven years, you know?

46:00.967 --> 46:06.096
I remarried after two years,
and you waited 67 years.

46:06.097 --> 46:07.891
Sixty-seven years. Wow.

46:10.143 --> 46:11.603
Mmm.

46:14.230 --> 46:15.273
Yeah.

46:21.488 --> 46:28.328
When eternity's on the line, one lifetime
of waiting seems like nothing.

46:30.205 --> 46:32.247
Jesus, you are so perfect.

46:32.248 --> 46:33.332
I'm not perfect.

46:33.333 --> 46:35.459
Oh, that's what perfect people say.

46:35.460 --> 46:37.461
Fine. I hate hearing about your kids

46:37.462 --> 46:39.463
and your grandkids
and the kids they had, okay?

46:39.464 --> 46:41.715
I mean, I don't-I don't hate them.

46:41.716 --> 46:42.717
Okay.

46:45.136 --> 46:47.764
But it kills me that I didn't get
to have all that with you.

46:53.144 --> 46:54.145
I'm glad you had it.

46:56.689 --> 46:58.441
I'm glad you had a happy life.

47:05.573 --> 47:08.159
I would go to the docks
waiting for you to return.

47:08.701 --> 47:11.286
Watching all the soldiers stream
onto shore,

47:11.287 --> 47:13.413
'cause I convinced myself
that they got it wrong.

47:13.414 --> 47:15.416
- That you would be among them. And…
- Joan.

47:18.336 --> 47:23.174
I would just sit and watch and wait.

47:27.595 --> 47:28.596
So I…

47:31.099 --> 47:32.850
I did wait for you, Luke.

47:36.271 --> 47:38.439
Yeah.

47:43.695 --> 47:44.778
Hmm.

47:44.779 --> 47:45.780
Hey.

47:47.907 --> 47:48.908
Come with me.

48:06.676 --> 48:10.346
If I wasn't already dead,
I'd be worried you're about to kill me.

48:13.891 --> 48:16.686
- Do you trust me?
- Oh. Sure.

48:17.729 --> 48:18.730
Come on.

48:22.942 --> 48:25.569
Hello, Mr. Fenwick.

48:25.570 --> 48:26.863
Just Fenwick.

48:28.197 --> 48:30.574
Right. Uh, we haven't been here before--

48:30.575 --> 48:32.535
Individual or shared?

48:34.621 --> 48:36.955
- Shared.
- Do not touch the exhibits.

48:36.956 --> 48:38.832
Remember, the exhibits aren't real.

48:38.833 --> 48:42.210
We take no responsibility
for emotional trauma.

48:42.211 --> 48:43.212
Happy reliving.

48:44.547 --> 48:45.631
You ready?

48:45.632 --> 48:46.633
For what?

49:00.271 --> 49:01.897
Every eternity has one.

49:01.898 --> 49:03.857
We call it archive tunnels.

49:03.858 --> 49:05.400
Which means?

49:05.401 --> 49:08.071
I don't know.
I've never been to an eternity before.

49:11.282 --> 49:12.784
We can find out together.

49:23.294 --> 49:25.004
- Hi. What's your name?
- Oh.

49:26.589 --> 49:27.882
- Yeah, you.
- Oh. I-I'm Joan.

49:28.758 --> 49:30.008
Yeah.

49:30.009 --> 49:31.510
What's your name?

49:31.511 --> 49:33.888
- Luke.
- Nice to meet you, Luke.

49:34.972 --> 49:36.807
- Oh, Luke.
- Joan's a pretty name.

49:36.808 --> 49:38.141
I haven't seen you around here before.

49:38.142 --> 49:41.144
Oh… …well,
I just moved to the city.

49:41.145 --> 49:43.146
Just around the corner. Briar…

49:43.147 --> 49:44.231
Briar cliff?

49:44.232 --> 49:45.233
Come on.

49:54.701 --> 49:57.370
- I was so nervous. Look at me.
- That's not what I'm saying--

49:57.954 --> 49:59.538
Look at you.

49:59.539 --> 50:01.791
Oh.

50:08.005 --> 50:10.674
Joan, I love you so much.

50:22.186 --> 50:23.187
Come on.

50:29.402 --> 50:31.236
Oh, nope. No, no.

50:31.237 --> 50:32.529
No. Luke, come on.

50:32.530 --> 50:35.741
- Oh, we're really going for it, eh?
- Hey.

50:35.742 --> 50:38.494
Stop!

50:57.221 --> 50:58.806
I don't wanna see this one.

51:03.686 --> 51:05.938
I love you.

51:15.656 --> 51:17.909
Worst day of my life.

51:28.127 --> 51:30.796
Luke.

51:30.797 --> 51:32.799
I missed you so much.

51:34.592 --> 51:35.593
Yeah.

52:02.078 --> 52:03.371
We should go.

52:04.413 --> 52:05.705
Luke, please.

52:05.706 --> 52:07.499
I don't remember this.

52:07.500 --> 52:11.002
- You don't need to see this.
- What's he doing at our dock?

52:11.003 --> 52:12.879
Can we just go please?

52:12.880 --> 52:14.381
Please…

52:14.382 --> 52:16.008
Oh, God, Luke. Please.

52:20.596 --> 52:22.347
Will you marry me?

52:22.348 --> 52:25.183
Of course.

52:25.184 --> 52:28.353
He made her death about him.
It's selfish, is what it is.

52:28.354 --> 52:32.149
- If you say so. So who's Karen?
- Oh, God. She's a neighbor.

52:33.150 --> 52:35.694
Longest-serving member
of the Oakdale Avenue HOA,

52:35.695 --> 52:37.655
and she won't let you forget it.

52:38.281 --> 52:40.407
She would always leave these
little sticky notes on my door.

52:40.408 --> 52:43.243
- She was a very passive-aggressive woman.
- Okay. Here we are. Here we are.

52:43.244 --> 52:44.954
- Gimme some space.
- Sorry.

52:49.333 --> 52:52.919
Larry. I heard about the pretzels.

52:52.920 --> 52:54.379
Karen. You're still old.

52:54.380 --> 52:57.008
I'm 72 now, thank you very much.

52:57.675 --> 52:58.758
Yeah, no.

52:58.759 --> 53:01.845
Sorry,
it's just a weird age to be your happiest.

53:01.846 --> 53:04.431
- You remember when Jim died?
- That was your happiest?

53:04.432 --> 53:06.641
- When your husband died?
- Oh, Jim was a dear.

53:06.642 --> 53:10.396
But anyway, that summer when I went on
that pottery retreat with my friend Barb…

53:11.272 --> 53:12.439
Right.

53:12.440 --> 53:13.857
Well, Barb and I were lovers.

53:13.858 --> 53:15.901
Oh. I-I didn't--

53:15.902 --> 53:20.030
I went full lesbian for three months,
and it was fabulous.

53:20.031 --> 53:24.284
But then I came back and I had the kids,
and the grandkids

53:24.285 --> 53:28.747
and the church group, and I just went
back into that miserable old closet.

53:28.748 --> 53:30.624
Oh, that explains
why you were so mean to me.

53:30.625 --> 53:32.334
Oh, no. I just didn't like you.

53:32.335 --> 53:33.501
Right.

53:33.502 --> 53:35.462
I came around eventually.

53:35.463 --> 53:38.965
- You grow on people, Larry.
- Mm-hmm.

53:38.966 --> 53:40.092
I'm thinking…

53:42.011 --> 53:43.261
Paris Land.

53:43.262 --> 53:47.265
It's basically Paris in the '60s,
but they speak English with an accent.

53:47.266 --> 53:48.851
And they have civil rights.

53:49.477 --> 53:51.102
I take it you're waiting on Joan.

53:51.103 --> 53:52.729
No, she's already here.

53:52.730 --> 53:54.815
Ooh, shit week for Oakdale.

53:55.524 --> 53:58.276
- So where you guys going?
- It's complicated.

53:58.277 --> 54:00.362
- Oh, are you gay too?
- Mmm.

54:00.363 --> 54:03.324
- Honestly, that would be easier.
- Look at you.

54:04.951 --> 54:07.786
You seem so uncomfortable.

54:07.787 --> 54:09.245
- Mm-hmm.
- Nah.

54:09.246 --> 54:10.538
- I-I'm hot.
- Think about it.

54:10.539 --> 54:12.791
The worst thing in the world
has already happened to you.

54:12.792 --> 54:14.459
He wishes.

54:14.460 --> 54:17.212
- Do tell.
- So, girl, this is what happened.

54:17.213 --> 54:19.339
Okay. L-Listen,
I came here to ask a question,

54:19.340 --> 54:21.007
and goddamn it,
I'm gonna ask Karen a question.

54:21.008 --> 54:22.301
Then ask the question.

54:23.177 --> 54:27.890
Karen, did Joan ever mention, um…

54:29.016 --> 54:30.768
Why do you think she fell in love with me?

54:35.147 --> 54:37.357
- Uh…
- Karen, say something.

54:37.358 --> 54:40.735
- Anything. Just say something.
- Well, I…

54:40.736 --> 54:43.321
- Um…
- Anything.

54:43.322 --> 54:46.199
I don't know.
She just did.

54:46.200 --> 54:48.410
I mean, I-I never thought

54:48.411 --> 54:50.870
she'd be happy again after Luke died…

54:50.871 --> 54:52.580
…but you made her happy.

54:52.581 --> 54:53.748
Mmm.

54:53.749 --> 54:56.459
You made your life about making her happy.

54:56.460 --> 54:59.254
- Isn't that enough?
- Eh.

54:59.255 --> 55:00.797
Luke is here.

55:00.798 --> 55:02.590
- Joan's Luke?
- Mm-hmm.

55:02.591 --> 55:06.011
Oh, he was so dreamy.

55:06.012 --> 55:07.971
I used to pretend I fancied him.

55:07.972 --> 55:10.765
- Of course, I didn't.
- Because you're a big, secret lesbian?

55:10.766 --> 55:11.975
- Exactly.
- Mmm.

55:11.976 --> 55:12.977
But, wow.

55:13.811 --> 55:14.894
He was perfect.

55:14.895 --> 55:16.771
Hey, listen to me.

55:16.772 --> 55:17.940
No one is perfect.

55:18.649 --> 55:19.733
No one is perfect!

55:19.734 --> 55:22.445
- Larry, don't be like that!
- No one is perfect!

55:23.029 --> 55:25.865
- Luke. Luke, would you calm down?
- About what?

55:26.532 --> 55:28.908
You know, if you just…

55:28.909 --> 55:32.287
If you think about it,
it was his way of saying

55:32.288 --> 55:34.497
that-that he knew that you
would always be a part of me.

55:34.498 --> 55:36.958
Come on, Joan. He wormed his way in.

55:36.959 --> 55:39.044
He manipulated you by using your grief.

55:39.045 --> 55:40.170
- No.
- He is such a leech.

55:40.171 --> 55:42.089
That is not what happened, okay?

55:42.757 --> 55:43.799
You left.

55:46.010 --> 55:47.178
I didn't leave. I died.

55:53.642 --> 55:56.270
Would you have said yes
if you weren't still grieving?

55:57.104 --> 55:59.315
I never stopped grieving.

56:01.901 --> 56:03.319
Would you say yes?

56:17.500 --> 56:19.292
Larry, Larry! Listen.

56:19.293 --> 56:21.920
I am rooting for you,
but this is not the way, okay?

56:21.921 --> 56:24.339
It's not even about him.
This is about you and Joan.

56:24.340 --> 56:27.300
The woman who you have loved
for 65 beautiful years,

56:27.301 --> 56:29.260
and have made her very happy.

56:29.261 --> 56:32.013
This is about showing that same woman
that you're willing

56:32.014 --> 56:35.225
to spend all of eternity together
to do the same thing.

56:35.226 --> 56:37.770
Now, is this gonna make her happy?

56:39.647 --> 56:40.939
- Okay, cool.
- What kind of creep

56:40.940 --> 56:41.898
leaves their door unlocked?

56:41.899 --> 56:45.360
- Maybe he doesn't have anything to hide.
- Nah, everybody's got something to hide.

56:47.279 --> 56:48.447
That's a little dramatic.

56:49.031 --> 56:51.282
It's actually really hard to keep
track of time here, so I applaud him.

56:51.283 --> 56:53.201
It's very practical.

56:53.202 --> 56:55.037
Larry, come on.

56:56.622 --> 56:58.790
Ha! Does a perfect person look at this?

56:58.791 --> 57:00.668
You've never looked at porn before, Larry?

57:03.170 --> 57:05.672
- Mm-hmm.
- Ah. What about this?

57:05.673 --> 57:07.215
Look at all these numbers.

57:07.216 --> 57:09.467
- Yeah, it's numbers.
- That one's got lipstick.

57:09.468 --> 57:11.010
- Mm-hmm.
- That means they're kissing.

57:11.011 --> 57:14.265
Yeah, it's been 67 years.
What would you do?

57:16.225 --> 57:19.435
Larry, come on. This is enough.
It's too much.

57:19.436 --> 57:21.729
Yeah. What am I doing? Let's go.

57:21.730 --> 57:23.274
- Let's just go.
- What the…

57:24.024 --> 57:25.567
You goddamn snake.

57:25.568 --> 57:27.652
Well, clearly the date
didn't go too well, did it?

57:27.653 --> 57:28.987
Oh, you took advantage of her.

57:28.988 --> 57:30.363
What're you talking about?

57:30.364 --> 57:33.116
You made your engagement about me.

57:33.117 --> 57:35.160
You used my death to worm your way in.

57:35.161 --> 57:37.579
- I don't have to listen to this.
- I felt awful leaving Joan alone.

57:37.580 --> 57:39.497
I genuinely hoped she would find someone.

57:39.498 --> 57:40.790
Yeah, right.

57:40.791 --> 57:42.960
But she woulda been
better off alone than with you.

57:43.544 --> 57:45.337
Well, I tried.

57:48.257 --> 57:50.008
Hey, is that hair dye?

57:52.887 --> 57:54.138
Stop!

57:55.681 --> 57:56.682
My nose!

57:59.768 --> 58:00.852
Get off of me!

58:00.853 --> 58:02.061
- Get off me!
- Get off me.

58:02.062 --> 58:04.648
That's it? That's all y'all can do?

58:07.902 --> 58:09.569
I didn't betray you, Luke.

58:09.570 --> 58:11.571
I didn't even know you.

58:11.572 --> 58:16.702
Yeah. Then why did you propose
at the dock?

58:20.122 --> 58:21.497
Larry.

58:21.498 --> 58:24.751
Trauma specialists
to Junction 145.

58:24.752 --> 58:26.044
Plane crash incoming.

58:26.045 --> 58:27.253
Baby formula. Here.

58:27.254 --> 58:28.880
- Sir…
- We also do breast milk.

58:30.132 --> 58:31.716
- Just a minute of your time. Please!
- Okay.

58:31.717 --> 58:33.676
- L-Let's get you somewhere quiet.
- Oh, God.

58:33.677 --> 58:35.888
- Bromance World.
- Why won't anybody come to Library World?

58:42.186 --> 58:44.939
Final call for High School World.

58:47.900 --> 58:49.735
What's wrong with these eternities?

58:50.736 --> 58:53.029
Oh, some are full.

58:53.030 --> 58:56.658
- Others are just out of fashion.
- Hmm.

58:56.659 --> 59:00.995
Quite a few of them weren't very PC by
today's standards.

59:00.996 --> 59:02.080
If that makes any sense.

59:02.081 --> 59:05.959
So, like, what happened to
the people inside of them?

59:05.960 --> 59:09.505
They are still in there
living out their afterlives.

59:10.923 --> 59:11.966
Right.

59:17.513 --> 59:18.806
Oh, God.

59:19.723 --> 59:22.268
I don't know what to do.

59:24.395 --> 59:28.439
You spent your entire life
worrying about other people.

59:28.440 --> 59:31.359
Now it's time to decide
what's best for you.

59:31.360 --> 59:32.361
Let me guess.

59:33.904 --> 59:35.364
Luke is best for me?

59:36.240 --> 59:39.743
I want you to choose Luke
because it's the life you missed.

59:40.869 --> 59:43.247
Eternity is a long time to have regrets.

59:44.748 --> 59:47.543
But that's your decision to make.

59:48.043 --> 59:50.336
Oh, God.

59:50.337 --> 59:53.840
What if I… What if I…
I don't know what to choose?

59:53.841 --> 59:55.801
Well, you need to figure it out.

59:56.927 --> 59:58.012
Sorry.

01:00:05.269 --> 01:00:08.188
Just have fun at the beach tomorrow.

01:00:08.772 --> 01:00:10.899
It is a paradise after all.

01:00:17.865 --> 01:00:19.700
I didn't think it would be this busy.

01:00:21.368 --> 01:00:24.245
- Yeah, it's fine.
- Very popular. It's okay.

01:00:24.246 --> 01:00:25.872
Wonder if we can get an umbrella.

01:00:25.873 --> 01:00:29.126
Yeah, you'd think that they would
hand one to you, huh? Or a chair?

01:00:34.631 --> 01:00:36.216
Look at the view.

01:00:43.349 --> 01:00:45.016
You were so beautiful, honey.

01:00:45.017 --> 01:00:46.351
Oh.

01:00:46.352 --> 01:00:48.728
I mean, you are beautiful.

01:00:48.729 --> 01:00:51.606
And you've always been beautiful,

01:00:51.607 --> 01:00:54.484
- you never stopped being beautiful.
- I get what you mean, love.

01:00:56.653 --> 01:00:59.656
You are right though.
This would've been a nice vacation.

01:01:00.699 --> 01:01:02.992
I mean, it doesn't have to be here.

01:01:02.993 --> 01:01:05.204
If you want another eternity, we can…

01:01:06.121 --> 01:01:07.789
We can go to space for all I care.

01:01:07.790 --> 01:01:09.750
As long as Luke's not floating around.

01:01:18.384 --> 01:01:20.552
You look pretty good yourself.

01:01:23.055 --> 01:01:24.555
Fore!

01:01:24.556 --> 01:01:26.015
That's golf, idiot!

01:01:26.016 --> 01:01:27.350
Okay, Larry, it's a child.

01:01:27.351 --> 01:01:28.893
Oh, he's-he's probably 90.

01:01:28.894 --> 01:01:30.354
I actually died when I was nine.

01:01:31.188 --> 01:01:32.688
- Oh.
- Oh.

01:01:32.689 --> 01:01:34.483
- Right.
- Hit and run.

01:01:35.359 --> 01:01:36.692
Least it was quick.

01:01:36.693 --> 01:01:37.694
It was not quick.

01:01:38.320 --> 01:01:42.490
It was very, very slow.

01:01:42.491 --> 01:01:44.535
- Oh.
- Get. Get.

01:01:45.202 --> 01:01:47.161
Hon, why don't we…
why don't we just get out of here.

01:01:47.162 --> 01:01:48.205
Okay.

01:01:54.044 --> 01:01:55.753
How was my funeral?

01:01:55.754 --> 01:01:57.171
Decent turnout?

01:01:57.172 --> 01:01:59.507
Yeah, you would've liked it.

01:01:59.508 --> 01:02:00.591
Really?

01:02:00.592 --> 01:02:03.094
Well, I mean, you would've
pretended to hate it, but it was nice.

01:02:05.681 --> 01:02:07.558
Zach did the eulogy.

01:02:08.183 --> 01:02:09.809
Did he try to be funny?

01:02:09.810 --> 01:02:13.480
Yeah, he did. He did try to be funny.
But, you know, it was sweet.

01:02:14.064 --> 01:02:16.567
The kids were-were so devastated.

01:02:17.860 --> 01:02:19.611
Who was the most devastated?

01:02:21.113 --> 01:02:24.283
I'm not answering that.

01:02:27.786 --> 01:02:29.788
Sweetie,
I'm sorry I wasn't there when you…

01:02:31.373 --> 01:02:32.374
You know.

01:02:33.208 --> 01:02:36.086
Yeah, but you were
waiting for me when I arrived.

01:02:41.216 --> 01:02:43.677
The kids will be happy
that we're together.

01:02:52.311 --> 01:02:53.519
Larry.

01:02:53.520 --> 01:02:54.521
Mmm?

01:02:56.190 --> 01:03:00.068
You have to understand
that I'm in an impossible situation.

01:03:02.779 --> 01:03:05.324
No. I don't understand.

01:03:06.366 --> 01:03:08.159
I understand you loved Luke.

01:03:08.160 --> 01:03:10.161
I loved Sally Daniels in the ninth grade.

01:03:10.162 --> 01:03:12.747
He wasn't some childhood crush, Larry.
He was my husband.

01:03:12.748 --> 01:03:15.917
Yeah, but we built a life together,
and now you just wanna throw it all away.

01:03:15.918 --> 01:03:19.170
Well, I never had a chance
to start a life with Luke, and…

01:03:19.171 --> 01:03:22.089
- you know, God, he waited 67--
- Sixty-seven years.

01:03:22.090 --> 01:03:24.217
Yeah, I get it.
I would've done the same thing.

01:03:24.218 --> 01:03:26.260
Well, you knew I was close.

01:03:26.261 --> 01:03:28.847
I was ready to wait
for as long as it took.

01:03:31.016 --> 01:03:32.683
I was.

01:03:32.684 --> 01:03:35.687
It's getting late.
We should head back, okay, honey?

01:03:41.109 --> 01:03:42.527
You're an idiot, Larry.

01:03:42.528 --> 01:03:43.903
Okay, hold on.

01:03:43.904 --> 01:03:45.404
I'm holding on.

01:03:45.405 --> 01:03:47.573
- You gotta shift your weight.
- Okay, okay.

01:03:47.574 --> 01:03:50.244
- Just don't hurt yourself, please.
- I know, but you're gonna tip us.

01:03:53.080 --> 01:03:57.416
♪ I can't forget you ♪

01:03:57.417 --> 01:04:00.963
♪ I've got these memories of you ♪

01:04:02.381 --> 01:04:05.634
♪ I can't forget you ♪

01:04:06.843 --> 01:04:10.389
♪ I'll always be loving you ♪

01:04:11.557 --> 01:04:15.352
♪ Once we were happy ♪

01:04:15.978 --> 01:04:18.604
♪ We were so carefree and gay ♪

01:04:18.605 --> 01:04:19.981
Come on, I wanna see the kids.

01:04:19.982 --> 01:04:21.774
But you take a wrong turn
in one of those things,

01:04:21.775 --> 01:04:23.484
you could be stuck in
your worst nightmare.

01:04:23.485 --> 01:04:26.571
Okay, what… Forget about it.
I just… I thought it could be fun.

01:04:26.572 --> 01:04:28.573
I-I know. I'm just…
I'm-I'm trying to protect you.

01:04:28.574 --> 01:04:31.200
No, you are protecting yourself.

01:04:31.201 --> 01:04:33.452
What're you so afraid you'll see?

01:04:33.453 --> 01:04:34.704
Hmm?

01:04:34.705 --> 01:04:36.122
It doesn't matter. It's fine.

01:04:36.123 --> 01:04:38.082
- You don't know what's going--
- Honey, it's okay.

01:04:38.083 --> 01:04:39.709
Gonna happen in there.

01:04:39.710 --> 01:04:42.253
Wait. Joan… I…

01:04:42.254 --> 01:04:43.630
Look. They look miserable.

01:04:54.099 --> 01:04:56.226
Larry, do you remember our first date?

01:04:57.352 --> 01:04:58.769
The flat.

01:04:58.770 --> 01:05:01.148
When we pulled over,
do you remember what you said?

01:05:01.940 --> 01:05:04.860
You said that, "This is
the perfect place for a flat tire.

01:05:05.402 --> 01:05:08.488
Wide shoulder, beautiful day, quiet road."

01:05:09.823 --> 01:05:11.742
Till I realized I didn't have a spare.

01:05:12.534 --> 01:05:14.494
Yeah, well, you never let me know it.

01:05:16.330 --> 01:05:18.956
You seemed so broken back then, honey.

01:05:18.957 --> 01:05:21.877
I-I felt like I needed
to be strong for you.

01:05:22.586 --> 01:05:24.546
I just wanted to make everything okay.

01:05:25.672 --> 01:05:27.883
Right down to that flat tire.

01:05:28.550 --> 01:05:30.135
And you did make everything okay.

01:05:31.887 --> 01:05:33.680
We had a wonderful life together.

01:05:42.314 --> 01:05:43.357
Come here.

01:06:05.087 --> 01:06:06.962
I don't care where we end up.

01:06:06.963 --> 01:06:08.924
Just as long as we're together.

01:06:18.392 --> 01:06:19.475
Okay.

01:06:19.476 --> 01:06:21.977
- So, uh, what-what's what's going on?
- What is…

01:06:21.978 --> 01:06:23.062
Yeah, what're you guys--

01:06:23.063 --> 01:06:24.855
I think it's important you hear
what Luke has to say.

01:06:24.856 --> 01:06:25.940
I'm so sorry, Larry.

01:06:25.941 --> 01:06:28.776
You should be, 'cause after
Larry broke into my apartment, I--

01:06:28.777 --> 01:06:31.237
- After he what?
- No, the door was open.

01:06:31.238 --> 01:06:32.405
- Was it?
- Jesus, Larry.

01:06:32.406 --> 01:06:34.824
- Not a big deal.
- What is your… Sorry, what is that?

01:06:34.825 --> 01:06:36.992
- Do the honors.
- Okay. Look, that I can ex…

01:06:36.993 --> 01:06:39.245
- I can explain. It's okay.
- It sounds way worse than it is.

01:06:39.246 --> 01:06:40.955
- "Dear Jo, I…" No.
- No. Give it to me.

01:06:40.956 --> 01:06:42.331
We don't need to do this right now.

01:06:42.332 --> 01:06:44.041
- Honey… Just give me…
- Joanie, I just wanted you to know

01:06:44.042 --> 01:06:46.085
- the truth about this man.
- Hey, I can… Let me talk--

01:06:46.086 --> 01:06:48.045
Oh, go grovel.

01:06:48.046 --> 01:06:52.091
Just… Okay. I know,
but it-it-it's out of context, honey.

01:06:52.092 --> 01:06:53.259
Yes, it is.

01:06:53.260 --> 01:06:54.720
I'm sorry, you said that…

01:06:55.220 --> 01:06:57.888
that you were willing
to wait as long as it took,

01:06:57.889 --> 01:06:59.765
but you-you couldn't
even last a measly week?

01:06:59.766 --> 01:07:01.058
I was. I honest… I…

01:07:01.059 --> 01:07:03.060
Um, I was trying
to set up our eternity, and--

01:07:03.061 --> 01:07:04.603
And you just assumed
that I would come find you?

